result.execSummary:
The defendant Jorge Luis Bonilla Galan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: **The Court has no objection to the sentence being served in another jurisdiction to include but not limited to the Jefferson County Jail** In the event probation is revoked, Defendant would be entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

Case Called @ 1:11 PM: Defendant Jorge Luis Bonilla Galan in court, in custody, appears via video.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant failed to appear at a prior motion hearing.  Defendant advised of right to counsel.  Court accepts voluntary waiver of counsel today.  Court entertains waiver of personal appearance.  Court accepts voluntary waiver of appearance in person.  Defendant does not contest State's motion to vacate PPDA and agrees agreement has been violated.  Court notes the filing of Jefferson Co case which probable cause was found and finds Defendant is in violation of the agreement and will act upon the NC plea previous entered.  JOC entered.  Arguments as to SEH by ADA.  No statement offered by Def.  The Court:  Accepts waiver of personal appearance.  Accepts resolution offered.  90 days WCJ - I/S (Huber, GT and 2 days TS Credt if revoked) - S/W - 1 yr probation.  Conditions of supervision:    The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; AODA and any follow thru; Court Costs plus DNA surcharge.  60 DTP or PP.    DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.  Right to expunge DNA record explained through the DOJ.  Appeal Rights Given.
